  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7 and boil a kettle</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>aubergine<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and<strong> potatoes </strong>(skin on) into thick slices</p>\r\n<p>Heat 1 tbsp <span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[2 tbsp]<strong>&nbsp;</strong></span><strong>olive oil</strong> in a large, wide-based pan (non-stick) over a high heat and cook the <strong>aubergine</strong> for 5 min on each side</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add&nbsp;250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span>&nbsp;boiled water to a pot (with a matching lid) and bring to the boil</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>stock cube<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[s]</span></strong>&nbsp;and stir to dissolve</p>\r\n<p>Add the sliced<strong> potatoes</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cover with a lid and cook&nbsp;for 10 min or until nearly tender, then drain (keep the <strong>drained stock</strong>) and leave to&nbsp;steam dry</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the cooked <strong>aubergine</strong> to a large baking dish in a single layer and season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p>\r\n<p>Place&nbsp;the dish into the oven for 10 min</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely dice the <strong>red onion<span style=\"color: #e86754;\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium-high heat with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\">&nbsp;[2 tbsp]</span>&nbsp;<strong>olive oil</strong></p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion</strong>,<strong> cinnamon</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>sugar </strong>and cook for 3 min or until softened</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>garlic</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>\r\n<p>Add the<strong> tinned tomatoes</strong> and the reserved <strong>potato stock</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/356.step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
